newsitem.title: USA: US Midco diesel, unleaded prices track NYMEX lower.
newsitem.headline: US Midco diesel, unleaded prices track NYMEX lower.

text.p: U.S. Midcontinent unleaded gasoline and diesel fuel prices eased on Monday, tracking lower NYMEX futures prices, traders said.
Differentials were steady as traders in the Chicago and Group Three markets assessed positions for March deliveries and waited for the heating oil and unleaded futures to bottom out, traders said.
"You might see some bottom pickers," one trader said of activity in the spot markets as trade opened for the week.

The Williams Pipeline system, a key barometer of inventories in the Group Three market, opened the week with a 36-day supply of low sulphur diesel and 25-day supply of unleaded gasoline on hand, traders said.
Low sulphur diesel for March deliveries was talked 5.75/6.0 cents a gallon over NYMEX April heating oil in Chicago and 4.0/4.25 cents over the print in Group Three.
High sulphur diesel also was steady at 3.0 cents a gallon over the print in Chicago and 2.25 cents over in Group Three.
